    "body": "I didn't see a tracking issue for supporting string arrays in the `winborder` option. The linked comment talks about waiting for support of array/dict option values, so I guess this is blocked by https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/32139.\n\n> I think this should be implemented after we support `array/dict` option vlaues. when border is an array it has too many extension possibilities in `nvim_oepn_win`.. currently it is also possible to support all the formats described in `nvim_open_win`, but this may make the code a bit complicated and not very meaningful. If we have an explicit markup in the option value such as =[xx] it may be much easier.  or other smart way which i missed ?\n\n_Originally posted by @glepnir in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31074#discussion_r1877456568_",
